s tiny amphibian is said to guide travelers to the fabled golden city. This association likely comes from the toxin secreted by the frog, which induces a debilitating sensitivity to light, giving the world around the victim a dazzling gilded sheen."],"Item":["0","44339"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","294"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1424":{"Text":["","On moonlit nights, this crustacean lifts its mighty pincers aloft, reaching out as if to pluck the pockmarked satellite right out of the sky. According to Yok Huy legend, specimens that successfully grasp the moon's image in their claws grow to be stronger and larger than their counterparts."],"":["0","7000"],"Item":["0","44340"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","9"],"FishingSpot":["0","297"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1425":{"Text":["","Considered a delicacy by the Hanuhanu, the preferred method of preparing this weighty crustacean is to simply place it atop a boiling cookpot and steam the crab, carapace and all."],"Item":["0","44341"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","301"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1426":{"Text":["","This beautiful, vibrant wavekin is beloved by the Xbr'aal, and, in times past, was enshrined as a deity in Ilyon Asoh. So profound was the villagers' reverence that they saw fit to ban fishing for the divine creature on all but a handful of days each year."],"Item":["0","44343"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","308"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1427":{"Text":["","Although known to also inhabit the Stardust Sea, this secretive wavekin favors the deep, briny waters of Xty'iinbek Tsoly. As such, sightings are few and far between."],"Item":["0","44342"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingSpot":["0","318"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1428":{"Text":["","Among the several species of cichlid native to the region, this particular specimen is often seen in the waters closest to the Boughs of Hwittayoanaan. Naturalists have posited that the wavekin's heightened olfactory senses lure it towards the Hhetsarro's open-air burial grounds."],"Item":["0","44345"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","2"],"FishingSpot":["0","319"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2517"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1429":{"Text":["","Deftly navigating the detritus-strewn waters at impossible speeds, there is nary an ilm of the driftdowns safe from this fearsome fish."],"":["0","7000"],"Item":["0","44346"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","2"],"FishingSpot":["0","324"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2519"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1430":{"Text":["","Reminiscent of the display panels utilized throughout Everkeep, the intricate patterns adorning this wavekin shift and shimmer as it swims. When exposed to an electrical current, these markings cycle through an exuberant myriad of colors, much to the delight of any onlookers."],"Item":["0","44344"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","327"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2519"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1431":{"Text":["","With its oversized dorsal fin and aerodynamic snout, this wavekin can be glimpsed soaring through the mists betwixt Yok and Xak Tural. Much like the clouds that blanket its natural habitat, the flesh of this toothsome fish is light and fluffy, making it a popular ingredient in a variety of local dishes."],"Item":["0","44347"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","700"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","5"],"FishingSpot":["0","322"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2517"],"IsInLog":["False","True"]}}}